.SH NAME
41, 41swara \- High-performance smart contract vulnerability scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B 41
[\fIPATH\fR]
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B 41swara
[\fIPATH\fR]
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B 41Swara Smart Contract Scanner
is a production-grade, fully offline vulnerability scanner designed for
Ethereum Foundation and blockchain security researchers. It performs static
analysis on Solidity smart contracts to detect security vulnerabilities,
with support for 150+ vulnerability patterns including real-world exploit
patterns from $3.1B+ in DeFi losses.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \[bu] 2
AST-based analysis with tree-sitter
.IP \[bu]
CWE/SWC ID mapping for compliance
.IP \[bu]
Confidence scoring (0-100%)
.IP \[bu]
L2 chain specific patterns (sequencer uptime, bridge security)
.IP \[bu]
Modern Solidity 0.8.20+ support (PUSH0, transient storage)
.IP \[bu]
DeFi-specific detectors (AMM, Lending, Oracle, MEV)
.IP \[bu]
Parallel scanning with 4-10x speedup
.IP \[bu]
Multiple output formats (text, JSON, SARIF)
.IP \[bu]
Slither and Foundry integration
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Basic Options"
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: \fBtext\fR (default), \fBjson\fR, or \fBsarif\fR
.TP
.BR \-\-min\-severity " " \fILEVEL\fR
Filter results by minimum severity: \fBcritical\fR, \fBhigh\fR, \fBmedium\fR, \fBlow\fR, \fBinfo\fR
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable detailed analysis output
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-threads " " \fIN\fR
Number of parallel threads (0 = auto-detect CPU cores)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Only show summary, suppress individual findings
.TP
.BR \-\-stats
Show performance statistics after scanning
.TP
.BR \-\-fail\-on " " \fISEVERITY\fR
Exit with code 1 if findings at or above severity threshold
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Save output to file instead of stdout
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output (useful for CI/CD logs)
.SS "Confidence & SWC Filtering"
.TP
.BR \-\-confidence\-threshold " " \fIPERCENT\fR
Only show findings with confidence >= PERCENT (0-100)
.TP
.BR \-\-include\-swc " " \fIIDS\fR
Only check specific SWC IDs (comma-separated, e.g., SWC-107,SWC-105)
.TP
.BR \-\-exclude\-swc " " \fIIDS\fR
Skip specific SWC IDs (comma-separated)
.SS "File Filtering"
.TP
.BR \-\-exclude\-pattern " " \fIGLOB\fR
Exclude files matching glob pattern (can be used multiple times)
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-file\-size " " \fIMB\fR
Skip files larger than specified size in MB (default: 10)
.SS "Baseline Comparison"
.TP
.BR \-\-baseline " " \fIFILE\fR
Compare against baseline JSON file (suppress known findings)
.TP
.BR \-\-export\-baseline " " \fIFILE\fR
Export current results as baseline JSON file
.SS "DeFi Analysis"
.TP
.BR \-\-defi\-analysis
Enable DeFi-specific analyzers (AMM, Lending, Oracle, MEV)
.TP
.BR \-\-advanced\-detectors
Enable advanced detectors (ERC4626, Permit2, LayerZero, L2, Uniswap V4, CCIP)
.SS "Tool Integration"
.TP
.BR \-\-slither\-json " " \fIPATH\fR
Combine with Slither JSON output for correlated analysis
.TP
.BR \-\-generate\-poc
Generate Foundry PoC tests for critical findings
.TP
.BR \-\-foundry\-correlate
Correlate findings with Foundry test results
.SS "Caching"
.TP
.BR \-\-cache
Enable incremental scanning cache (skip unchanged files)
.TP
.BR \-\-cache\-dir " " \fIDIR\fR
Cache directory (default: .41swara_cache)
.SS "ABI Analysis"
.TP
.BR \-\-abi
Enable ABI security analysis mode for JSON ABI files
.SS "Git Integration"
.TP
.BR \-\-git\-diff
Scan only modified .sol files (compared to git HEAD)
.TP
.BR \-\-git\-branch " " \fIBRANCH\fR
Branch to compare against (default: HEAD)
.SS "Continuous Monitoring"
.TP
.BR \-\-watch
Watch mode - automatically rescan on file changes
.SS "Professional Features"
.TP
.BR \-\-audit
Generate professional audit report
.TP
.BR \-\-project " " \fINAME\fR
Project name for audit report (requires --audit)
.TP
.BR \-\-sponsor " " \fINAME\fR
Sponsor/client name for audit report (requires --audit)
.TP
.BR \-\-project\-analysis
Enable cross-file vulnerability analysis
.TP
.BR \-\-report
Generate clean markdown report
.SS "Version & Help"
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Print version number
.TP
.BR \-\-version\-full
Show full version with build details and feature list
.TP
.BR \-\-examples
Show usage examples
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information
